Billion Year Spree series: Billion Year Spree: The History of Science Fiction (1973) BSFA special award[39] Trillion Year Spree: The History of Science Fiction (1986), with David Wingrove, a revised and expanded version of Billion Year Spree Winner of the 1987 Hugo Award for the year's best nonfiction.[1] At the 'Conspiracy 87' ceremony, Aldiss began his acceptance speech by holding the Hugo aloft and proclaiming, to general approbation, "It's been a long time since you've given me one of these, you bastards!"[55]
Billion Year Spree: The History of Science Fiction (1973) BSFA special award[39]
Trillion Year Spree: The History of Science Fiction (1986), with David Wingrove, a revised and expanded version of Billion Year Spree Winner of the 1987 Hugo Award for the year's best nonfiction.[1] At the 'Conspiracy 87' ceremony, Aldiss began his acceptance speech by holding the Hugo aloft and proclaiming, to general approbation, "It's been a long time since you've given me one of these, you bastards!"[55]
